# PulangAman mobile build procedure

## API target (compile-time)

`AppConfig` in `apps/mobile/lib/core/config.dart` uses `String.fromEnvironment` — URLs are **baked in at build time**, not read at runtime.

| Target | When to use |
|--------|-------------|
| **Cloud (default)** | Normal testing, parent/child on real devices or emulators |
| **Local** | Only when `services/api` runs on the host (`npm run dev`) |

**Cloud defaults** (no extra defines needed):
- API: `https://pulangaman-api.onrender.com`
- WS: `wss://pulangaman-api.onrender.com`
- Auth: `USE_DEV_AUTH=true` (default)

**Local override** (Android emulator → host machine):
```bash
--dart-define=API_BASE_URL=http://10.0.2.2:3000 \
--dart-define=WS_BASE_URL=ws://10.0.2.2:3000 \
--dart-define=USE_DEV_AUTH=true
```

Never ship a build that points at `10.0.2.2` unless the user explicitly tests against a local API.

## Standard cloud APK build + install

Run from `apps/mobile`. Always **rebuild and reinstall** after config or native changes; hot reload does not update `dart-define` values.

```bash
cd apps/mobile
flutter build apk --debug --dart-define=USE_DEV_AUTH=true
```

Install (pick device with `adb devices`):

```bash
# Parent (emulator)
adb -s emulator-5554 shell am force-stop com.tursinalabs.pulangaman
adb -s emulator-5554 install -r build/app/outputs/flutter-apk/app-debug.apk
adb -s emulator-5554 shell am start -n com.tursinalabs.pulangaman/.MainActivity

# Child (physical Pixel — serial may differ)
adb -s 3A251FDJG0045D install -r build/app/outputs/flutter-apk/app-debug.apk
```

Package: `com.tursinalabs.pulangaman`

## `flutter run` (dev)

Same defines as above. For cloud testing, defaults are enough:

```bash
flutter run -d emulator-5554 --dart-define=USE_DEV_AUTH=true
```

Full restart required after changing `--dart-define` or `config.dart` defaults.

## Google Maps

Maps tiles need `GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY` in `android/local.properties` **and** optional `--dart-define=GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=...` for in-app banner. Rebuild after key changes.

## API changes (Render)

Mobile-only changes do **not** update the server. If the task touches `services/api/`:

1. Commit and `git push origin main` (Render auto-deploys from `render.yaml`).
2. Wait for deploy; verify: `curl https://pulangaman-api.onrender.com/health`
3. Then rebuild/install the Flutter app if the client depends on new endpoints.

Migrations run on start: `npm run migrate && node dist/index.js`.

## Agent checklist

- [ ] Confirm target: cloud vs local API
- [ ] `flutter build apk` (or `flutter run`) with correct defines
- [ ] Install on the device the user named (parent emulator vs child phone)
- [ ] If API was changed, push to Render and verify `/health` before mobile smoke test
- [ ] Do not commit secrets (`.env`, `local.properties` keys)
